[[File:Star_Wars_RPG_Battle_Armor.jpg|thumb|An example of battle armor]]
'''Battle armor''' was some of the heaviest [[Armor/Legends|armor]] in widespread use as of the [[Jedi Civil War]]. Designed for use by heavy militias, it had the protection needed to keep a soldier alive during ranged combat with massive weapons.

Battle armor was constructed from a mesh of [[Metal/Legends|metal]] or composite plates and a padded [[Jumpsuit/Legends|jumpsuit]]. Variants of the armor included less plates and more padding for a lighter, though less protective armor, and heavier plating with molded pieces to fit the wearer. Though the armor was available unmodified, most users personalized their armor, usually cobbling together gear from various sources.<ref name="RPG-Core">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook]]''</ref>

Battle armor was also used in other eras. During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], battle armor was a classification of armor. [[Stormtrooper/Legends|Stormtrooper]] armor was an example of battle armor, as well as much of the armor used by [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]].

